
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-thomson-domain-auth-01.txt'>
    <title>"Domain Authorization for PIDF-LO", Martin Thomson, James Winterbottom</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-thomson-domain-auth-01.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes a standard method for digitally signing Presence Information Data Format Location Object (PIDF-LO) documents using a subset of the XML Digital Signature specification. A digital signature enables the user of a signed PIDF-LO document to attribute that information to an authorized source within the domain of the target entity. A schema is defined for including a domain authorization element in the PIDF-LO and a set of XML Path Language (XPath) filters for selecting the correct elements for signing.</description>
    <dc:date>2005-06-28T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
